參考書目 References


備註 Remarks





基本素養 Basic Literacy
□ 參與大體感恩追思，教導學生尊重生命。
 Through the opening and gratitude ceremonies, students are expected to learn the spirit of respecting life.
□ 訪視大體老師家屬，培養同理心與服務學習精神。
 Through visiting the donator's family, students are expected to learn the empathy and the spirit of service-learning.
□ 陪伴家屬進行大體入殮，體現社會關懷。
 Through accompanying the donator's family, students are expected to learn the spirit of caring the community.
□ 鼓勵學生參予國際學術報告，並邀國外學者訪問交流，與世界接軌。
 Students are encouraged to participate in international academic meeting and communicate with invited foreign scholars.
 

核心能力 Competence
■ 具有充實的解剖學(含大體解剖學、組織學、胚胎學、神經解剖學、細胞生物學等)知識，並具有純熟練達之大體解剖技術與教學經驗。
 Students are expected to learn basic knowledge, dissecting skill and teaching experience of anatomy, including human gross anatomy, histology, embryology, neuroanatomy and cell biology.
■ 具有專業的研究能力，熟悉各種解剖學與細胞生物學的研究設備及技術，推動生命科學之整合與研究。
 Students are expected to familiarize a variety of anatomy and cell biology research equipment and techniques in order to promote the integration of life science research.
■ 具有創造力、邏輯思考與獨立研究能力。
 Students are expected to learn the capabilities of creativity, logical thinking and independent research.
■ 成為善於表達自己的年輕學者。
 Students are expected to become articulated young scholars.
□ 具有國際觀並能使學術研究國際化。
 Students are expected to develop global perspectives in both academic and research.
 

課程概述 Course Description
       介紹人體神經系統的解剖構造與形態，內容涵蓋中樞、周邊、與自主神經系統的組成結構、血管分佈、以及感覺與運動神經之傳導路徑。本課程將深入探索神經系統中特定區域所扮演的生理功能並以相關之臨床常見病徵輔助說明。The intent of this course is to introduce the human nervous system with an emphasis on its structures and functional connections. This course covers a variety of topics pertinent to the morphology, motor and sensory pathways, vasculature, as well as clinical correlations of the central and peripheral nervous systems.     

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
Indentify brain and spinal cord structures with their orientations in detailRecognize the sensory and motor system functionsCorrelate the anatomical structures and the functions 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Chap 2 & 3-Orientation；Cerebral topography；Midbrain/Hindbrain2National Holiday3大體老師 感恩追思會4Chap 29 & 30-Cerebral cortex；Hemispheric asymmetries；Laboratory I5Chap 13-Autonomic nervous system6Chap 15 & 16-Spinal cord；Laboratory II7SPRING BREAK8Chap 17-Brainstem9Chap 23 & 28-Cranial nerves II, III, IV, VI & visual pathways10Laboratory Review11Chap 18~22-Cranial nerves V, VII, VIII, IX, X, XI & XII12Midterm Examination (lectures & labs)13Chap 24 & 25-Reticular formation；Cerebellum14Chap 26 & 27-Diencephalon:Hypothalamus，Thalamus & Epithalamus15Chap 33-Diencephalon:Basal ganglia16Chap 34-Limbic system & Olfactory system17Chap 35-Clinical correlation:Cerebrovascular disease18Final Examination (lectures only) 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


